Q: MAUI .NET Set Window Size A: <p>A few years later, but this came up first thing on my search. Using VS 2026, Create Maui Project. All this became just a couple lines of code.</p>
<p>In the App.xaml.cs that is created for you, it already has the CreateWindows override. Simply change...</p>
<pre><code> protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState activationState)
 {    
     return new Window(new AppShell());
 }
</code></pre>
<p>to</p>
<pre><code>        protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState activationState)
        {
            Window myWindow = new Window(new AppShell());


            if (OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
            {
                myWindow.Width = 800;
                //myWindow.Height = 600;
            }

            return myWindow;

        }
</code></pre>
